A 15-year-old boy was killed after his bicycle collided with an Isuzu bakkie in Oakford &#8211; Verulam, on Thursday afternoon. At approximately 14:56 members of Reaction Unit South Africa were dispatched to the scene after receiving a call from a member of public reporting the incident. Upon arrival the teenager was found to have sustained life threatening injuries.He succumbed to his injuries before the paramedics could arrive.It is alleged that the boy was riding his bicycle at high speed downhill when he collided head on into an Isuzu bakkie that was travelling in the opposite direction. The force of the impact cause the bicycle to split into two pieces. The driver of the bakkie was not injured.